This paper deals with the study of binary linear codes and their structure, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The concept of cyclic shifts is also relevant in coding theory (cs.CC) and signal processing (cs.SD). Additionally, the paper involves the use of polynomials, which is a common tool in numerical analysis (cs.NA).
